WEBVTT

00:00.418 --> 00:14.616
You know, if you're just joining us, we have been working our way this fall through a series called Long Journey Home, looking at the journey of Israel from their time of captivity, bondage in Egypt until they made it to the Promised Land.

00:14.636 --> 00:17.219
Now, we're getting real close to the end of the series.

00:17.259 --> 00:20.042
In fact, next Sunday, we're going to finally make it to the Promised Land.

00:20.663 --> 00:29.394
But before we get there, I'm just wondering if you have ever met one of those people who just seems to have it all.

00:29.986 --> 00:39.095
You know, they've got, they're smart, they're talented, they're attractive, they're athletic, they've got a charismatic personality.

00:39.715 --> 00:40.976
Have you ever met someone like that?

00:41.657 --> 00:42.478
I mean, other than me.

00:43.118 --> 00:50.085
I once read a book by a guy named Brent Hansen called Unoffendable.

00:50.726 --> 00:56.511
And in it, he tells a story of one of those people who just seems to have it all.

00:57.052 --> 00:59.634
And he calls the guy the ultimate dude.

00:59.746 --> 01:03.891
And let me just read for you his description of the ultimate dude.

01:04.932 --> 01:06.674
He says, I once met the ultimate dude.

01:07.475 --> 01:15.483
I was in Afghanistan working with the hospital network, Cure International, and they assigned him as security to make sure I didn't get killed.

01:16.084 --> 01:17.666
Let me describe his awesomeness.

01:18.587 --> 01:21.390
He can speak Dari the local language because he's smart.

01:22.211 --> 01:24.854
He's also six foot four and in perfect condition.

01:25.675 --> 01:28.658
He can handle weapons because he's a special forces veteran.

01:29.026 --> 01:31.150
He's got combat experience.

01:31.170 --> 01:35.036
He also looks like John Hamm and appears no lie 20 years younger than he is.

01:35.998 --> 01:37.100
Did I mention he was smart?

01:37.741 --> 01:42.990
He's owned restaurants, apartment buildings, and several very successful medical businesses in the United States.

01:43.891 --> 01:49.501
And he's an inventor, developing tactical wear for dozens of militaries and police forces worldwide.

01:50.042 --> 01:51.785
So yeah, he's impressive.

01:52.526 --> 01:54.770
Well, I forgot to mention he's theologically astute.

01:55.234 --> 01:58.979
His dad was chairman of the board at one of the top seminaries in the United States.

01:59.480 --> 02:02.104
And oh yeah, he played big time college football.

02:02.705 --> 02:05.288
He started on a defensive line for a big 12 team.

02:06.290 --> 02:14.441
He does walk with a slight limp, but even that seeming vulnerability becomes impressive when you hear the story of how you heard it jumping out of a helicopter on a mission.

02:16.284 --> 02:17.666
So I'm already feeling inferior.

02:19.008 --> 02:23.474
But when he walked in to Cures Hospital, the top plastic surgeon at the hospital,

02:23.586 --> 02:31.457
Afghanistan's top docked at healing children from disabilities, Kim running over to us, shouted the ultimate dude's name, and embraced him.

02:32.098 --> 02:32.378
Why?

02:32.418 --> 02:36.544
Because the ultimate dude taught him how to do plastic surgeries at the hospital.

02:38.527 --> 02:39.468
He's a surgeon too.

02:41.771 --> 02:42.392
One of the best.

02:43.153 --> 02:44.234
I neglected to mention that.

02:45.316 --> 02:48.781
By the way, when I met the ultimate dude, he was getting ready for his wedding.

02:49.602 --> 02:52.626
He was marrying a runner up in the Miss Universe contest.

02:55.074 --> 03:00.763
Some of the celebrity friends would be there, like best-selling international thriller authors who use him to help shape stories.

03:01.644 --> 03:02.686
I'm not making this guy up.

03:02.726 --> 03:04.368
He really exists.

03:04.388 --> 03:05.270
And I really like him.

03:06.131 --> 03:09.296
He's such a great guy and a huge blessing to people in many countries.

03:10.177 --> 03:13.302
Cures healed so many children, done so much for the least of these.

03:13.883 --> 03:15.906
And the ultimate dude has been part of that.

03:16.767 --> 03:17.488
It's all amazing.

03:18.269 --> 03:23.858
If I were that guy, I would have a hard time not just walking around thinking, I'm so awesome, I can barely stand it.

03:25.858 --> 03:39.996
So he's a Christian and also a great looking, tall, athletic, wealth-making, beauty queen marrying, special forces serving, celebrity befriending, weapons bearing, multiple language speaking, business starting, cutting edge equipment inventing, world hopping, child saving, plastic surgeon.

03:41.437 --> 03:42.319
And there's one more thing.

03:43.340 --> 03:44.041
He's insecure.

03:46.584 --> 03:47.465
He told us as much.

03:48.366 --> 03:49.407
He really struggles with it.

03:49.447 --> 03:54.674
He feels as though he's trying to live up to something and he doesn't know what and he feels he's falling short.

03:55.650 --> 04:00.097
I'm so thankful for his honesty, that my first thought was actually great.

04:00.517 --> 04:02.020
Now he's authentic and likable too.

04:05.785 --> 04:11.253
Well today we're going to consider another ultimate dude, a guy named Caleb.

04:12.275 --> 04:16.081
The first time Caleb is mentioned is in the book of Numbers, chapter 13.

04:16.141 --> 04:22.290
And this is where we read the story about Moses sending spies into the promised land to scope it out.

04:22.722 --> 04:30.994
And God has already told them the land is going to be theirs, that he's going to go before them, he's going to go with them, he's going to give them the victory.

04:31.896 --> 04:37.744
And the despised job is simply to do some advanced reconnaissance, getting ready for this mission.

04:38.245 --> 04:39.727
So here's how the story begins.

04:41.250 --> 04:47.198
The Lord spoke to Moses saying, send men to spy out the land of Canaan, which I'm giving to the people of Israel.

04:47.920 --> 04:52.306
From each tribe of their fathers, you shall send a man, everyone achieved among them.

04:52.898 --> 04:53.979
So Moses sent them.

04:54.620 --> 04:58.345
From the tribe of Judah, Caleb, the son of Defuna.

04:59.146 --> 05:05.334
Now the first thing we learn about Caleb is that he is a chief within the tribe of Judah.

05:06.075 --> 05:13.765
So in terms of qualifying as an ultimate dude, Caleb's first star on his resume is that he's a recognized leader.

05:14.266 --> 05:16.128
He's a recognized chief.

05:16.849 --> 05:20.434
Now I don't know what image that evokes in your mind when you think about a chief.

05:20.898 --> 05:24.902
But if you're thinking big feathered headdress, that's not what it's about.

05:25.843 --> 05:31.330
We learn a bit more about what this chief title means from a story in Exodus chapter 18.

05:32.231 --> 05:36.956
And it is the story of a father-in-law who is meddling in his son-in-law's business.

05:37.777 --> 05:40.039
The father-in-law's name is Jethro.

05:40.580 --> 05:43.163
And his son-in-law is a guy named Moses.

05:43.863 --> 05:46.226
And here's what we find in Exodus chapter 18.

05:48.322 --> 05:53.631
The next day Moses sat to judge the people and the people stood around Moses from morning till evening.

05:54.873 --> 06:01.004
When Moses' father-in-law saw all that he was doing for the people, he said, what is this that you're doing for the people?

06:01.705 --> 06:05.892
Why do you sit all alone and all the people stand around you from morning till evening?

06:07.234 --> 06:11.762
And Moses said to his father-in-law, because the people come to me to inquire of God.

06:12.162 --> 06:18.731
When they have a dispute, they come to me and I decide between one person and another and I make them know the statutes of God and His laws.

06:20.313 --> 06:23.557
Moses' father-in-law said to him, what you're doing is not good.

06:24.719 --> 06:29.225
You and the people with you will certainly wear yourselves out for the thing is too heavy for you.

06:29.265 --> 06:31.448
You're not able to do it alone.

06:32.749 --> 06:33.671
Now obey my voice.

06:34.271 --> 06:36.274
I will give you advice and God be with you.

06:37.058 --> 06:45.988
You shall represent the people before God and bring their cases to God, and you shall warn them about the statutes and the laws and make them know the way in which they must walk and what they must do.

06:47.270 --> 07:01.906
Moreover, look for able men from all the people, men who fear God, who are trustworthy and hate-a-bribe, and place such men over the people as chiefs of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties, and of tins.

07:03.170 --> 07:05.373
and let them judge the people at all times.

07:05.594 --> 07:10.441
Every great matter they shall bring to you, but any small matter they shall decide themselves.

07:11.263 --> 07:15.129
So it will be easier for you and they will bear the burden with you."

07:16.691 --> 07:17.553
Not a bad plan.

07:18.414 --> 07:21.739
Did you spot that word, chiefs?

07:23.482 --> 07:28.370
Based on this passage, I take it that Caleb was one of those chiefs.

07:29.011 --> 07:31.154
Maybe we would call him a judge.

07:31.298 --> 08:00.434
uh... justice of the peace uh... civil court judge in particular and from jethro's outline would appear that there was uh... an appeals court process uh... there were some judges uh... judges of tens who handled very minor matters you know my neighbors goat eight my laundry but but then there were judges over fifties there are judges over hundreds above them there were judges or chiefs over thousands and when all else failed to resolve the problem

08:00.514 --> 08:04.860
it would get to Moses, kind of an appeals court process if you will.

08:06.002 --> 08:10.929
Now I don't know what level of jurisdiction Caleb was overseeing.

08:11.931 --> 08:24.509
Although based on the significance of the responsibility he was entrusted with as a representative spy for the very powerful tribe of Judah, I would guess that he ranked a fair bit higher than District Court.

08:26.011 --> 08:27.794
What stands out to me in terms of

08:28.002 --> 08:33.329
ultimate dude qualifications are the traits that apparently qualified him to serve as a judge.

08:34.070 --> 08:36.473
First we find that he is a proven leader.

08:37.054 --> 08:39.998
So look for able men among all the people.

08:40.899 --> 08:44.284
And then we find out that he was also one who feared God.

08:45.145 --> 08:48.970
He was faithful, he was devout, and he was a man of integrity.

08:49.511 --> 08:53.396
So look for people who are trustworthy, people who hate a bribe, they can't be bought.

08:54.979 --> 08:57.522
So Caleb is a guy with legal clout,

08:58.114 --> 08:59.716
In a big title, he's a chief.

09:00.697 --> 09:01.638
He's a proven leader.

09:01.958 --> 09:03.420
He has demonstrated wisdom.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.562
He's a man of genuine faith.

09:05.762 --> 09:09.446
His character is sterling silver, but that's not all.

09:09.466 --> 09:12.509
A couple of weeks ago, we talked about Joshua.

09:12.909 --> 09:18.355
And Joshua, your call was another of those 10 spies who were sent in to check out the land.

09:20.337 --> 09:24.882
Ultimately, Joshua would succeed Moses and end up being Caleb's boss.

09:25.666 --> 09:29.130
But on that spying mission, they were just two dudes with a job to do.

09:30.411 --> 09:37.599
And of course, the fact that they were seeing as good candidates for a spy mission behind enemy lines means that they weren't just average dudes.

09:38.240 --> 09:40.922
They were kind of the ancient version, I think, of Navy SEALs.

09:41.883 --> 09:46.989
And so, after this ultimate dude's list of qualifications, he had courage.

09:48.050 --> 09:50.132
He's a guy who's an accomplished leader.

09:50.933 --> 09:52.094
He has great wisdom.

09:52.815 --> 09:53.876
He has a deep faith.

09:53.936 --> 09:55.378
He has sterling character.

09:56.034 --> 09:57.596
and he has steely-eyed courage.

09:59.198 --> 10:08.329
But what really set Joshua and Caleb apart from the rest of SEAL Team Six wasn't the message, wasn't the mission, the mission itself.

10:09.530 --> 10:12.554
It was the intelligent assessment they gave when they got back.

10:13.735 --> 10:17.820
You recall that eight of the special operators came home with their tails between their legs.

10:18.821 --> 10:22.706
They said, yeah, the land looks good, but the enemies are too strong.

10:23.330 --> 10:27.395
their cities, their fortifications are just too good.

10:27.996 --> 10:29.598
Their weapons are too powerful.

10:29.698 --> 10:34.944
And if we obey God's order to attack, this is going to be nothing but a suicide mission.

10:36.506 --> 10:39.290
But it was Joshua and Caleb who had a completely different take.

10:40.772 --> 10:47.640
They saw all the same dangers as the other eight, but they also had complete confidence in their secret weapon.

10:49.002 --> 10:50.023
That was God's promise.

10:51.525 --> 10:52.306
And if they're

10:52.386 --> 10:55.911
Great commander was telling him it was time to jump.

10:57.193 --> 11:03.201
Their only question was, how high and how long would you like us to stay aloft, sir?

11:05.164 --> 11:06.406
You know how that all turned out?

11:08.268 --> 11:15.939
Because the people in mass bought into the panic report, God said that none of them would ever be allowed to enter into the promised land.

11:17.021 --> 11:17.842
Only their children.

11:18.338 --> 11:25.490
A fresh generation would be given that privilege and so began that famous 40-year trek of attrition.

11:26.712 --> 11:31.901
Israel was forced into this nomadic holding pattern waiting for that generation to pass.

11:33.283 --> 11:34.585
But there were two exceptions, right?

11:35.367 --> 11:36.849
Joshua and Caleb.

11:36.869 --> 11:39.794
We find in Numbers, chapter 32.

11:40.610 --> 11:42.392
The Lord's anger was kindled that day.

11:42.412 --> 11:53.504
He swore saying, surely, none of the men who came up out of Egypt from 20 years old and upward shall see the land that I swore to give to Abraham, to Isaac and to Jacob, because they have not holy followed me.

11:54.365 --> 12:03.856
None except Caleb, the son of Jafuna, the Kennesite, and Joshua, the son of none, for they have holy followed the Lord.

12:04.357 --> 12:09.202
Now I want you to keep your eye on that little phrase right there and see if it shows up anywhere else.

12:10.114 --> 12:10.975
Deuteronomy 1.

12:11.035 --> 12:21.152
The Lord heard your words and was angered and he swore not one of these men at his evil generation, so see the good land I swore to give to your fathers except Caleb the son of Jafuna.

12:21.773 --> 12:26.060
He shall see it and to him and to his children I will give the land on which he has trodden.

12:26.380 --> 12:26.701
Why?

12:26.721 --> 12:30.066
Because he has wholly followed the Lord.

12:32.354 --> 12:37.960
Caleb himself, I was 40 years old when Moses, the servant of the Lord sent me from Kedish, Barnia, to spy out the land.

12:38.341 --> 12:44.467
And I brought him word again as it was in my heart, but my brothers who went up with me made the heart of the people melt.

12:44.888 --> 12:47.991
Yet I, holy, followed the Lord.

12:48.031 --> 13:00.084
Moses swore on that day saying surely the land at which your foot is trodden should be an inheritance for you and your children forever because you have holy followed the Lord my God.

13:00.525 --> 13:01.586
Still Caleb talking.

13:03.042 --> 13:07.709
Then Joshua blessed him and he gave Hebron to Caleb the son of Jifuna for an inheritance.

13:07.729 --> 13:17.765
Therefore Hebron became the inheritance of Caleb the son of Jifuna the Kennesite to this day because he wholly followed the Lord, the God of Israel.

13:19.407 --> 13:23.894
That appears to have been the defining trait of Caleb.

13:25.156 --> 13:29.202
It wasn't just his courage, it wasn't his smarts, it wasn't his political savvy.

13:29.762 --> 13:34.829
What set Caleb apart was that he was a man who wholly followed the Lord.

13:35.950 --> 13:36.671
But that's not all.

13:37.853 --> 13:46.264
The day comes after those 40 years are completed that unbelieving generation have all been given their last rights, all except Joshua and Caleb.

13:47.286 --> 13:50.750
And it lasts as time to cross the Jordan and commence the conquest.

13:51.972 --> 13:55.757
Of course, Joshua and Caleb are not spry young warriors.

13:56.398 --> 13:59.602
That was 40 years ago that they were those guys.

14:00.226 --> 14:02.048
Joshua now is commander in chief.

14:02.489 --> 14:07.515
So obviously he'll be doing his fighting from a command post rather than a foxhole.

14:08.356 --> 14:11.439
But then there's Caleb, our ultimate dude.

14:12.200 --> 14:15.384
Just check out his RFO, his request for orders.

14:15.865 --> 14:16.846
Joshua 14.

14:17.887 --> 14:19.769
Today I'm 85 years old.

14:20.710 --> 14:23.654
I'm as strong now as I was when Moses sent me on that journey.

14:24.255 --> 14:27.218
And I can still travel and fight as well as I could then.

14:27.874 --> 14:30.217
So give me the hill country that the Lord promised me.

14:31.299 --> 14:36.186
You remember that as scouts, we found the descendants of Anak living there in great walled towns.

14:37.107 --> 14:42.434
But if the Lord is with me, I will drive them out of the land just as the Lord said.

14:43.816 --> 14:46.480
We already knew this guy was courageous and a fighter.

14:47.601 --> 14:50.846
The old seal team vet is still eager for the fight.

14:51.807 --> 14:53.710
And not just any fight, it's the toughest fight.

14:54.551 --> 14:56.754
He says, you recall when I spied this out originally,

14:56.962 --> 15:00.588
That's where the biggest enemies were, let me at him.

15:01.810 --> 15:05.596
85 years old and he still swears he can take a man half his age.

15:06.478 --> 15:09.182
Probably with one hand tied behind his back just to make it fair.

15:11.366 --> 15:14.070
So Caleb, our ultimate dude is a chief.

15:14.090 --> 15:15.132
He's a proven leader.

15:15.192 --> 15:16.574
He's a wise judge.

15:16.654 --> 15:18.157
He's a man of strong faith.

15:18.197 --> 15:19.339
He's a courageous warrior.

15:20.000 --> 15:23.666
And he is a senior citizen who is still fighting fit.

15:25.250 --> 15:27.632
But there was one more trait I want to add to this list.

15:29.074 --> 15:30.095
And that is humility.

15:31.136 --> 15:32.617
I don't know if he spotted the little phrase there.

15:32.637 --> 15:36.941
He said, if the Lord is with me, I will drive them out.

15:38.542 --> 15:39.643
Caleb knew his abilities.

15:41.005 --> 15:42.626
He knew he was a chief among his people.

15:43.988 --> 15:49.993
He knew why only he and Joshua, among all of their peers, were still around to even have this conversation.

15:50.053 --> 15:52.475
God had rewarded him for his faithfulness.

15:53.997 --> 15:55.218
He knew his own abilities.

15:56.322 --> 16:04.113
I'm guessing he showed up to this meeting with Joshua in short sleeves and flexed just a little to show the fact that he could still do the job.

16:06.095 --> 16:07.097
But he also knew his limits.

16:08.699 --> 16:15.969
He wasn't afraid of a fight, but he knew the enemies in that hill country really were more than he could handle.

16:17.010 --> 16:20.055
He had seen all the same things the other eight spies had seen.

16:21.076 --> 16:25.522
And the things that had scared him, he understood the odds they were up against.

16:26.690 --> 16:31.596
And he knew the only way he could charge those gates of hell and win would be if the Lord was with him.

16:33.318 --> 16:40.287
I have a hunch that long ago in the very first battle that Israel faced against the marauders of Amalek.

16:41.549 --> 16:44.212
Caleb must have been one of the warriors that Joshua chose.

16:45.333 --> 16:46.375
He'd been in that fight.

16:47.196 --> 16:48.958
And you recall how that battle went, right?

16:49.018 --> 16:55.506
The deciding factor in their triumph was tied to Moses who was seated atop this hill

16:55.778 --> 17:01.764
holding aloft the staff of God, the physical symbol of God's presence and power to deliver his people.

17:03.485 --> 17:12.754
Caleb had seen the moments when Moses' arms retired, and the staff began to lower, and suddenly Caleb found himself losing ground.

17:13.515 --> 17:21.202
But then he had seen, as Moses again, with the help of his friends, began to raise that staff high, how Caleb began to get the better of the enemy.

17:22.944 --> 17:24.946
And I think that vivid visual lesson

17:25.730 --> 17:29.794
of unseen spiritual realities had burned itself into Caleb's memory.

17:31.235 --> 17:40.824
And as he anticipated combat with even stronger enemies, his confidence was not in his flex, but it was in the Lord.

17:40.845 --> 17:46.270
The phrase that had defined so much of his life was defining him still.

17:47.591 --> 17:51.034
It was a man who wholly followed the Lord.

17:52.376 --> 17:54.898
And if the Lord was leading him to go up those hills,

17:56.002 --> 17:57.143
Caleb was eager to follow.

17:59.646 --> 18:05.052
The story Caleb has always grabbed my attention because he was unique.

18:06.594 --> 18:09.236
You don't just run into ultimate dudes every day.

18:10.538 --> 18:12.300
I have known some very smart people.

18:13.341 --> 18:20.068
I've known some talented people, some courageous people, some noble people, some physically strong people.

18:20.088 --> 18:25.394
I was telling someone the other night, a friend of mine who was in the seminary had been a trainer for the Seahawks.

18:25.666 --> 18:30.032
And we got talking to him one day, and we just said, so just how big and how strong are those guys?

18:30.833 --> 18:31.834
They say, well, I'll tell you a story.

18:31.894 --> 18:34.678
He said that the Hawks were playing the game.

18:34.698 --> 18:37.101
They got to halftime, and they weren't doing well.

18:37.441 --> 18:42.988
And some calls had gone against him, and one of the linemen came in, and he was really hot.

18:43.008 --> 18:44.290
He was torqued.

18:44.310 --> 18:49.277
And he comes storming into the locker room, and there's a full coke machine standing there in the locker room.

18:49.917 --> 18:53.522
And this guy grabs the machine, picks it up, and throws it on the floor on its face.

18:54.626 --> 18:55.908
Yep, that's pretty big, all right.

18:58.531 --> 19:00.093
But those are people that I meet every day.

19:02.336 --> 19:04.840
And if I do, they are notable.

19:06.662 --> 19:12.230
Brent Hansen said of his encounter with that other ultimate dude, he said, meeting one of them can make you feel inferior.

19:13.872 --> 19:18.859
But I don't think the point of Caleb's story is to make us feel inferior.

19:20.220 --> 19:21.642
It's to inspire us.

19:22.884 --> 19:24.466
There are things about Caleb

19:24.834 --> 19:30.544
that I think were uniquely his, which may or may not even be in the realm of possibility for me or for you.

19:32.106 --> 19:34.350
Those are the things where I can feel inferior.

19:35.732 --> 19:48.333
You can learn wisdom, but let's face it, some people are just gifted with being able to see the big picture and to think strategically in ways that I am awed by.

19:48.373 --> 19:51.218
You may be courageous.

19:52.386 --> 19:54.649
But that really has nothing to do with being bigger strong.

19:54.729 --> 19:58.574
I've known big strong guys who fainted at the side of blood.

19:59.495 --> 20:06.083
And I've known little petite nurses that can walk into scenes of incredible trauma and just calmly do what needs to be done.

20:08.646 --> 20:15.415
I've known people have risen through the ranks and gotten job promotions and titles as much because of who they knew as what they could do.

20:15.435 --> 20:18.258
I can't match that.

20:20.194 --> 20:25.300
And when it comes to good health, I have seen health food fanatics that drop dead at young ages with heart attacks.

20:26.421 --> 20:29.824
And I've known lifelong smokers who were still stinking up the room in their 90s.

20:32.187 --> 20:35.651
So genetics has a lot to do with who is still flexing at 85.

20:35.991 --> 20:43.679
The thing I want to focus on from the story like Caleb's is what he can teach me beyond just natural ability.

20:45.041 --> 20:46.162
What was true of him

20:46.722 --> 20:50.827
that can inspire us, that can instruct us on our own long journey home.

20:52.790 --> 21:00.240
What if a life-changing things were true of him that I believe can be true of anyone, regardless of natural abilities?

21:02.002 --> 21:05.527
If you've been tracking with me, I think you already know what the answers are.

21:06.608 --> 21:07.509
Two things I'd say.

21:08.631 --> 21:14.258
One, he wholly followed the Lord, and he humbly followed the Lord.

21:15.266 --> 21:18.710
Neither one of those things is dependent on natural abilities.

21:20.031 --> 21:28.400
To holy and humbly follow the Lord to give him yourself with whatever you have to give and to do whatever it is he's asking you to do.

21:28.440 --> 21:44.818
On the teaching survey that went out several weeks ago, I really appreciate all the inputs, several people expressed an interest in hearing me teach on how to finish well, how to run the course of life well.

21:45.474 --> 21:46.856
And I love that question.

21:46.956 --> 21:53.125
I've often said that there are many people who move to swim with the intent to stop doing things.

21:54.467 --> 21:57.171
That's retirement communities tend to have that happen a lot.

21:58.213 --> 22:09.530
And yet I am so grateful that in this congregation with a lot of ages, but a lot of you represent the demographic of people who may have come here and at one level could have said, I don't want to do anything anymore.

22:09.550 --> 22:12.594
I see people who are fully engaged.

22:13.538 --> 22:16.303
People who are asking that question, how do I finish well?

22:17.365 --> 22:19.088
Young adults saying, how do I live well?

22:19.208 --> 22:20.811
Parents saying, how do I parent well?

22:21.973 --> 22:25.019
Older adults saying, how do I finish this race well?

22:27.643 --> 22:32.211
Caleb was this senior saint who kept saying, it ain't over till it's over.

22:33.995 --> 22:35.858
What do you want me to do, Lord?

22:37.378 --> 22:44.586
abilities and strength may change, but that heart that is ready to holy and humbly follow the Lord is key.

22:45.847 --> 22:52.835
And whatever the ability is and whatever stage of life you're in, that is a heart that God desires in all of us.

22:56.038 --> 23:01.024
Also for all ages and stages, the call of the gospel is to follow the Lord.

23:02.245 --> 23:03.186
It begins

23:03.298 --> 23:07.343
facing the reality that there are enemies that we cannot overthrow in our own strength.

23:09.185 --> 23:10.607
It's not just enemies out there.

23:12.209 --> 23:21.460
The gospel challenges me to look in the mirror and recognize that the enemy that so often defeats me and hurt others is right here in me.

23:23.062 --> 23:29.810
Jesus once told a group of very self-righteous, religious professionals that they were like a person

23:29.986 --> 23:37.258
criticizing others because they had a speck of sawdust in their eye and they didn't realize that there was a plank sticking out of their own.

23:38.941 --> 23:46.233
They were so blind to their own faults that it made their snobby, self-righteous critiques of others laughable.

23:48.036 --> 23:52.123
The Apostle Paul described this personal dilemma like this from Romans 7.

23:52.143 --> 23:56.690
It says, I know that nothing good lives in me.

23:57.186 --> 23:58.528
That is in my sinful nature.

23:58.608 --> 24:00.450
I want to do what is right, but I can't.

24:01.071 --> 24:02.773
I want to do what is good, but I don't.

24:03.874 --> 24:07.198
I don't want to do what is wrong, but I do it anyway.

24:08.620 --> 24:12.084
Paul says one of the enemies I fight with isn't out there.

24:13.126 --> 24:15.168
It's the enemy that I deal with in here.

24:16.370 --> 24:26.482
I think anyone who has a modicum of introspection and self-awareness would say, oh yeah, that's usually where the bigger fights are, the harder fights.

24:27.490 --> 24:28.791
But no, Paul didn't give up hope.

24:30.433 --> 24:37.722
Like Caleb, he understood his own inability to overcome such an enemy, but he also knew that with God's help, victory was possible.

24:38.583 --> 24:43.869
He went on to say this, who will free me from this life is dominated by sin and death?

24:44.930 --> 24:49.555
Thank God, the answer is in Jesus Christ, our Lord.

24:50.977 --> 24:55.442
See, the gospel calls us into the fight by calling us to cry out to God

24:55.746 --> 25:02.112
for the help that only He can give, to put our faith in what Jesus has done for us at the cross.

25:03.794 --> 25:11.902
And maybe you're someone who's come this morning and this whole thing of faith and a relationship with Jesus is nothing you've ever embraced for yourself.

25:12.963 --> 25:18.909
And maybe you're thinking that what it takes for God to accept you and to love you is that you've got to earn it.

25:18.949 --> 25:20.770
You've got to prove yourself to Him.

25:22.472 --> 25:24.434
And I just want to let you know that

25:24.866 --> 25:26.648
That's not how we win his approval.

25:28.070 --> 25:32.374
The people you're sitting with, quite honestly, are just a bunch of failures.

25:36.198 --> 25:42.365
Me among them, we have not been rescued by God because we were doing so well.

25:43.466 --> 25:46.069
Jesus came because we weren't doing well at all in ourselves.

25:46.990 --> 25:50.354
The message of grace is that he has come for us.

25:51.618 --> 25:56.786
But just because we have stepped into a walk of faith, that doesn't mean that the battle just ends.

25:57.507 --> 25:59.270
We're going to talk next week about the Promised Land.

25:59.290 --> 26:03.878
We're going to talk about the fact that Israel getting into the Promised Land was not the end of the battle.

26:04.879 --> 26:07.464
In many ways, it was just the beginning of more battles.

26:08.746 --> 26:10.328
And yet we don't fight the battle alone.

26:10.368 --> 26:14.214
And Paul, who knew himself, said, man, I feel this battle in myself.

26:14.755 --> 26:15.777
How am I ever going to win?

26:15.797 --> 26:18.962
He said, I'm going to win because of Jesus.

26:19.842 --> 26:25.848
I'm going to win because he's with me and because I want to holy and humbly follow him and trust him.

26:28.991 --> 26:30.012
But it doesn't stop there.

26:30.112 --> 26:35.216
For Caleb to fully claim the land he was promised, he had to step up to the fight.

26:36.117 --> 26:38.419
This isn't a passive thing we're being called to.

26:39.561 --> 26:46.647
Jesus calls us into a walk of faith, but is a walk that does indeed call us to step into our own fight.

26:47.588 --> 26:49.650
Here's what Jesus said to his disciples.

26:50.466 --> 26:58.177
Jesus said to his disciples, if any of you wants to be my follower, you must give up your own way, take up your cross, and follow me.

26:58.217 --> 27:02.503
If you try to hang on to your life, you will lose it.

27:03.444 --> 27:06.648
But if you give up your life for my sake, you will save it.

27:08.571 --> 27:13.458
And what do you benefit if you gain the whole world but lose your own soul?

27:14.619 --> 27:16.562
Is anything worth more than your soul?

27:17.954 --> 27:24.060
Do you know what kept everyone, almost everyone, in Caleb's generation from experiencing the promised land?

27:25.522 --> 27:30.346
They got hung up trying to save their own lives through their own efforts.

27:32.488 --> 27:33.670
What was different about Caleb?

27:35.351 --> 27:37.934
Well, it wasn't just natural ability that we had plenty of that.

27:37.994 --> 27:39.515
It wasn't a lucky promotion.

27:39.535 --> 27:42.498
It wasn't just good genetics or great hair.

27:42.538 --> 27:46.162
It was simply a day-to-day decision

27:46.274 --> 27:52.364
to holy and humbly trust the Lord and do whatever it was God asked him to do.

27:54.106 --> 27:55.709
So what would that look like for you this week?

27:58.193 --> 28:01.117
Where is God asking you to follow him?

28:01.137 --> 28:01.999
Or are you even asking?

28:03.301 --> 28:04.142
Maybe you should do that.

28:06.025 --> 28:07.708
What would it look like to take up your cross?

28:09.190 --> 28:14.258
What would it look like to step into sacrifice and obedience to him?

28:16.258 --> 28:23.550
What are you clinging to that feels like safety but may actually be a source of great loss?

28:26.215 --> 28:33.948
Is there something or someone that deep in your heart you think to yourself, I could never let go of that?

28:35.430 --> 28:42.322
That you just keep clutching onto so tightly because somehow you believe that that is really the source of your security and your safety.

28:44.642 --> 28:46.645
Or maybe there's a grudge that you keep harboring.

28:48.647 --> 28:53.253
And to think about forgiveness either scares you or makes you mad.

28:54.735 --> 29:01.263
Because you're convinced that if you were to actually forgive to release that you might never get justice.

29:02.805 --> 29:03.946
And so we hold on to it.

29:05.168 --> 29:09.573
And we let it have a place in our heart, a hard place, an angry place.

29:12.137 --> 29:13.298
Maybe there's some marker.

29:14.338 --> 29:28.834
some status symbol, some point of pride that we find ourselves willing to compromise for or even live a double life to protect because we want to convey a certain image to other people.

29:29.395 --> 29:32.378
We want them to see us a certain way even though it's not true.

29:32.398 --> 29:42.610
And we're afraid to ever be honest and transparent about who we are because that ego, that pride matters more.

29:45.378 --> 29:54.748
Maybe there is some personal agenda that you're allowing to tear apart the relationships in your life because you just have to have it your way.

29:56.090 --> 30:07.623
And having your way has become more important than humbling yourself and loving others and maybe taking up a cross and following Jesus in that relationship.

30:11.167 --> 30:14.290
You don't have to be an ultimate dude.

30:15.714 --> 30:16.956
or an ultimate doodad.

30:19.399 --> 30:23.385
All Jesus is asking us to do is what Caleb did.

30:24.567 --> 30:29.995
It's to holy and humbly trust him and follow him.

30:31.197 --> 30:37.747
Let's pray.

30:37.767 --> 30:45.298
Father forgive us for the times that we excuse our own complacency

30:46.786 --> 30:55.939
our laziness, sometimes our cowardice, on the basis that we just can't be that kind of person.

30:56.880 --> 31:02.988
That those must be unique superhero people and we could never walk in their footsteps or do the things they did.

31:05.832 --> 31:15.826
Father forgets for hiding behind those things, I pray that you would grant us the faith, you would grant us the courage to trust you.

31:17.442 --> 31:20.386
to follow you, wherever, whatever that means.

31:21.387 --> 31:26.533
Whatever stage of life we're in, Lord, let us follow that part of Caleb's example.

31:28.455 --> 31:32.560
Let us be people who holy and humbly follow after you.

31:34.923 --> 31:40.049
Lord, I believe your Holy Spirit is probably saying different things to different people all through this room.

31:42.352 --> 31:44.274
I pray, Lord, you give us ears to hear.

31:45.442 --> 31:48.045
and hearts that are willing to trust you and to obey.

31:48.125 --> 31:53.171
Lord, what the world would see is not ultimate dudes.

31:55.334 --> 32:02.323
Lord, could they see in us the changes it makes when people are willing to holy and humbly follow after you?

32:03.304 --> 32:04.165
To follow Jesus.

32:05.887 --> 32:08.370
I ask this in Jesus name, amen.

